                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scribe="EggEir001" script="unknown"><p>According to a note by
                                        <foreign>sýslumaður</foreign>
                                    <name type="person" key="JonJak001">Jón Jakobsson</name> on fol.
                                    3v, the priest <name type="person" key="EggEir001">Eggert
                                        Eiríksson</name> wrote the first five
                                        <foreign>rímur</foreign> cantos of <title type="uniorm"
                                        >Pontus rímur</title> (ff. 4r-114v).</p></handNote>
                            <handNote scribe="SveSol002" script="unknown">and <name type="person"
                                    key="SveSol002">Sveinn Sölvasson</name> wrote the rest of the
                                    <foreign>rímur</foreign> cantos.</handNote>
                            <handNote scribe="PalBen001" script="unknown">According to a note by
                                    <name type="person" key="RasRas001">Rasmus Rask</name> on fol.
                                221r, <title type="uniform">Hænsa-Þóris rímur</title> (fols
                                193r-221r) is written by <name type="person" key="PalBen001">Páll
                                    Benediktsson</name>: <q xml:lang="is">allar þessar rímur hefir
                                    uppskrifad Páll Benediktsson á Túngu</q></handNote>
                            <handNote scribe="BenSig001" script="unknown">The
                                    <foreign>rímur</foreign> on fols 223r-91v are the author <name
                                    type="person" key="BenSig001">Benedikt Sigurðsson</name>'s
                                autographs.</handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>Marginalia by Rasmus Rask and Jón Jakobsson. Fols 289-91 have varying
                                dates and signatures by the author Benedikt Sigurðsson. </p>
                        </additions>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>Written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in <origDate
                                notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799">the eighteenth century</origDate>.
                            Benedikt Sigurðsson provieded his <foreign>rímur</foreign> (ff. 223-91)
                            with dates and signatures, all of these were finished in the years
                                <origDate notBefore="1722" notAfter="1725">1722-25</origDate>. The
                            dates provided by Sveinn Sölvason (ff. 1-192) are from <origDate
                                notBefore="1760" notAfter="1779">the 1760-1770s</origDate>.</origin>
                        <provenance>According to <name type="person" key="JonJak001">Jón
                                Jakobsson</name>'s notes on fol. 3v and 192r, Sveinn Sölvasson gave
                            fols 4-192 (<title type="uniform">Pontus rímur</title> and <title
                                type="uniform">Gissurar rímur Þorvaldssonar</title>) to Jón's wife,
                                <name type="person" key="SigSte001">Sigriður Stefánsdóttir</name>,
                            in <date when="1765">1765</date> and <date when="1780">1780</date>,
                            respectively.</provenance>
                    </history>
